1)	When we go to our repository in the remote we can see the commit link. If we click that it shows how many commits happened along with the commit command.
2)	If we want to create file directly in remote then click “CreateNewFile”.
3)	Enter the content in the text box. 
4)	Below there under commit new file, enter the commit comment as “Creating lesson_3_reflections.txt directly in remote GitHub”
5)	Click Commit New File.
